In my main.ts:

``` javascript
import { bootstrap } from '@angular/platform-browser-dynamic';
import { enableProdMode } from '@angular/core';
import { ElectronAngularBoilerplateAppComponent, environment } from './app/';
```

which gets transpiled into

``` javascript
"use strict";
var platform_browser_dynamic_1 = require('@angular/platform-browser-dynamic');
var core_1 = require('@angular/core');
var _1 = require('./app/');
```

I've tried just editing those requires in my transpiled JS file, and it just looks like all my requires have the wrong paths for electron.
1. Is what I'm trying to do possible?
2. Can I give electron a 'root path' so that it stops trying to load from `/` by default?

OKAY! I think I got it to work:

``` javascript
    require('./system-config.js');
    require('./main.js');

    //  System.import(__dirname + '/system-config.js').then(function () {
    //   System.import(__dirname + '/main.js');
    // }).catch(console.error.bind(console));
```

I don't know why I can't use the systemjs imports, but commenting them out seems to have worked... I hope that does't come back to bite me later.
